'''阿列克謝二世'''（[[俄語|俄語]]：{{lang|ru|Патриарх Московский и всея Руси Алексий II}}，{{bd|1929年|2月23日|2008年|12月5日|catIdx=Alexy II}}），是第15任[[莫斯科大牧首|莫斯科和全俄大牧首]]。世俗名'''阿列克谢·里迪格'''<ref name="BN">{{cite web|url=http://www.orthodox.ee/indexeng.php?d=history/palex|title=PATRIARCH ALEXY II OF MOSCOW AND ALL RUSSIA Biographical note|accessdate=2008-12-06|author=|date=|work=|publisher=orthodox.ee|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081208203344/http://www.orthodox.ee/indexeng.php?d=history%2Fpalex|archivedate=2008-12-08|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 。

==生平==
阿列克谢·里迪格出生於[[愛沙尼亞|愛沙尼亞]]的[[塔林|塔林]]。其父米哈伊尔·里迪格是[[波罗的海德意志人|波罗的海德意志人]]。他的祖先海因里希·尼古拉·鲁丁格是[[瑞典|瑞典]]杜纳蒙德（Dünamünde，今[[拉脫維亞|拉脫維亞]]首都[[里加|里加]]市域內）地区驻防军的指挥官。并于1695年被瑞典王[[卡尔十一世|卡尔十一世]]授予[[骑士|骑士]]的荣誉。18世纪[[大北方战争|大北方战争]]之后，瑞典的[[爱沙尼亚|爱沙尼亚]]、[[立陶宛|立陶宛]]都被俄罗斯帝国吞并。弗雷德里希·威廉·冯·鲁丁格（阿列克谢的高祖父）在[[叶卡捷琳娜二世|叶卡捷琳娜二世]]统治期间皈依[[东正教|东正教]]。<ref>The spelling of the names here is [[transliteration|transliteration]] from Russian in the Patriarch's official biography – [http://www.pravenc.ru/text/64696.html АЛЕКСИЙ II] ''Orthodox Encyclopaedia'' (2000)</ref> 

1917年[[十月革命|十月革命]]后，阿列克谢与父亲逃难到了爱沙尼亚并安定下来。先是在[[哈普沙卢|哈普沙卢]]，教士拉尔夫·冯·祖尔穆勒收留了他们。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muuseum.haapsalu.ee/index.php?aasta=19&lk=40 |language=et |title=Chronology |accessdate=2008-12-05 |publisher=Museum of Laanemaa |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081208165228/http://www.muuseum.haapsalu.ee/index.php?aasta=19&lk=40 |archivedate=2008-12-08 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>而后米哈伊尔搬到了[[塔林|塔林]]。1926年，米哈伊尔结识伊莲娜·约瑟霍夫娜并与其结了婚。

阿列克謝二世在[[愛沙尼亞共和國|愛沙尼亞共和國]]度過了他的童年。從幼年開始，他便受[[大司祭|大司祭]]伊望·博戈亞夫冷斯基的教導。他於愛沙尼亞的俄語學校受教育。在蘇聯於1940年吞併愛沙尼亞之後，阿列克謝與家人險遭蘇聯當局逮捕，但他們當時躲到了一間小破屋中，得以倖免。<ref name="EJ">{{Cite news |first=Aarne |last=Vahter |language=et |coauthors= |title=Eestlane juhtis 80 miljonit õigeusklikku |url=http://www.ekspress.ee/2008/12/05/varia/5734-eestlane-juhtis-80-miljonit-oigeusklikku |work= |publisher=ekspress.ee |date=2003-02-04 |accessdate=2008-12-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207202517/http://www.ekspress.ee/2008/12/05/varia/5734-eestlane-juhtis-80-miljonit-oigeusklikku |archive-date=2009-02-07 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>德國佔領愛沙尼亞期間，阿列克謝與父親米哈伊爾（已經於1942年12月20日成為教士）共同負責慰問俄軍戰俘。由於在德軍之下幫助戰俘有助於其反蘇聯宣傳，他們的行為受到了德軍的允許。蘇聯重新奪回愛莎尼亞後，他們選擇了留在愛莎尼亞，而不是像其他波羅的海德意志人一樣，遷徙至西歐。<ref name="EJ"/>二戰期間，[[斯大林|斯大林]]復興了俄羅斯正教會，在戰時關閉的[[亚历山大·涅夫斯基主教座堂_(塔林)|亚历山大·涅夫斯基主教座堂]]也在1945年蘇聯接管愛沙尼亞後重新開放。成為蘇聯公民後的阿列克謝，於1946年成為了亚历山大·涅夫斯基主教座堂的辅祭。隨後他分別在該教堂與塔林[[喀山聖母像|喀山聖母像]]教堂擔任了[[圣詠集|圣詠集]]的朗讀者。<ref name="BN"/>

阿列克謝在[[列寧格勒|列寧格勒]]專心研究神學，1961年升任為主教，1964年成為大主教；1990年[[蘇聯解體|蘇聯解體]]前夕成為莫斯科大牧首。在位期间，他將分散在全俄各地的東正教教會都統一在莫斯科大牧首的領導之下，並且使[[俄羅斯東正教|俄羅斯東正教]]恢复了蘇聯時期喪失的道德權威，東正教和[[羅馬天主教|羅馬天主教]]的關係也有所好轉。不過他在很多問題上引起爭議。

== 與克格勃 ==
根據一些資料及人士，包括[[格列布·亞庫寧|格列布·亞庫寧]]和[[叶夫戈尼娅·阿爾巴茨|叶夫戈尼娅·阿爾巴茨]]<ref name="CWNrep" /><ref name="Andrew">[[Christopher_Andrew_(historian)|Christopher Andrew]] and [[Vasili_Mitrokhin|Vasili Mitrokhin]], The [[Mitrokhin_Archive|Mitrokhin Archive]]: The KGB in Europe and the West, Gardners Books (2000), ISBN 0-14-028487-7</ref><ref name="Albats">[[Yevgenia_Albats|Yevgenia Albats]] and Catherine A. Fitzpatrick. ''The State Within a State: The KGB and Its Hold on Russia — Past, Present, and Future''. 1994. ISBN 0-374-52738-5, page 46.</ref><ref name="Church">[[Konstantin_Preobrazhenskiy|Konstantin Preobrazhenskiy]] – [http://cicentre.com/Documents/putin_espionage_church.html Putin's Espionage Church] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081209002520/http://cicentre.com/Documents/putin_espionage_church.html |date=2008-12-09 }}, an excerpt from a forthcoming book, "Russian Americans: A New KGB Asset" by [[Konstantin_Preobrazhenskiy|Konstantin Preobrazhenskiy]]</ref> 的說法，阿列克謝二世曾為克格勃工作。<ref>[http://www.krotov.info/spravki/persons/20person/ridiger.html Alexiy Ridiger], by Yakov Krotov</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Felix Corley  |title=Patriarch Alexy II: Priest who stayed close to the Kremlin while guiding the Russian Orthodox Church into the post-Soviet era |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/patriarch-alexy-ii-priest-who-stayed-close-to-the-kremlin-while-guiding-the-russian-orthodox-church-into-the-postsoviet-era-1054454.html|publisher=[[The_Independent|The Independent]] |date=8 December 2008 |accessdate=6 December 2008 | location=London| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081207082812/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/patriarch-alexy-ii-priest-who-stayed-close-to-the-kremlin-while-guiding-the-russian-orthodox-church-into-the-postsoviet-era-1054454.html| archivedate= 7 December 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref><ref name="CWNrep">[http://www.cwnews.com/news/viewstory.cfm?recnum=13868 Confirmed: Russian Patriarch Worked with KGB] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/61AYfNXXv?url=http://www.catholicculture.org/news/features/index.cfm?recnum=13868 |date=20110824050010 |dateformat=iso }}, Catholic World News. Retrieved 29 December 2007.</ref><ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/1999/feb/12/1 Russian Patriarch "was KGB spy"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/61AYeWxIV?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/1999/feb/12/1 |date=20110824045957 |dateformat=iso }} [[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] 12 February 1999</ref><ref>[http://www.demokratizatsiya.org/Dem%20Archives/DEM%2001-04%20armes.pdf Chekists in Cassocks: The Orthodox Church and the KGB] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071008041146/http://www.demokratizatsiya.org/Dem%20Archives/DEM%2001-04%20armes.pdf |date=2007-10-08 }} – by Keith Armes, [[Demokratizatsiya_(journal)|Demokratizatsiya]]</ref><ref>[http://www.demokratizatsiya.org/Dem%20Archives/DEM%2007-01%20mcgann.pdf The Russian Orthodox Church under Patriarch Aleksii II and the Russian State: An Unholy Alliance?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080227100701/http://www.demokratizatsiya.org/Dem%20Archives/DEM%2007-01%20mcgann.pdf |date=2008-02-27 }} – by Leslie L. McGann, [[Demokratizatsiya_(journal)|Demokratizatsiya]]</ref> 克格勃的檔案顯示他的代號是DROZDOV。然而，在1980年之前，幾乎所有人，不管他們屬於什麼單位或者與克格勃有無關係，都被克格勃加上了代號，並沒有特殊性。<ref name="CWNrep" /> 叶夫戈尼娅·阿爾巴茨所查閱的克格勃檔案顯示阿列克謝二世於1988年受到了克格勃領導的表揚。<ref name="Albats"/>又根據愛沙尼亞克格勃的檔案，阿列克謝二世成功地壓制了一些反抗政權的修士。<ref name="SvPokr">[http://online.wsj.com/article/SB118469533202469128.html Cold War Lingers At Russian Church In New Jersey] By Suzanne Sataline, [[Wall_Street_Journal|Wall Street Journal]] 18 July 2007.</ref>這一檔案是一本關於一位克格勃人員的傳記式檔案，並且其記錄與阿列克謝的生平相符合。儘管俄羅斯正教會否認這些檔案的真實性。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/1999/feb/12/1|title=Russian Patriarch 'was KGB spy'|date=12 February 1999|accessdate=11 December 2008|publisher=[[Guardian.co.uk|Guardian.co.uk]]|location=London|archive-date=2011-08-24|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/61AYeWxIV?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/1999/feb/12/1|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

俄羅斯正教會長期以來否認阿列克謝與克格勃有關聯。<ref>"Official spokesman for the Moscow Patriarchy Father Vsevolod Chaplin labeled such reports as "absolutely unsubstantiated" in a Wednesday interview with Interfax. "There is no data indicating that Patriarch Alexy II was an associate of the special services, and no classified documents bear his signature," he said. "I do not think that direct dialogue between the current patriarch and KGB took place," Father Vsevolod continued. However, "all bishops communicated with representatives of the council for religious matters in the Soviet government, which was inevitable, since any issue, even the most insignificant one, had to be resolved through this body. It is quite another matter that the council forwarded all its materials to the KGB," he said." [http://www.stetson.edu/~psteeves/relnews/0009b.html Moscow Patriarchate Rejects Times Report of Alexy II'S Collaboration with KGB, Sept 20, 2000 (Interfax)] "Chaplin, the church spokesman, said in March, "Nobody has ever seen a single real document that would confirm the patriarch used his contacts with Soviet authorities to make harm to the church or to any people in the church." [http://www.stetson.edu/~psteeves/relnews/0205e.html Russia's Well-Connected Patriarch, Washington Post Foreign Service , 23 May 2002] {{Wayback|url=http://www.stetson.edu/~psteeves/relnews/0205e.html |date=20170307130303 }}; "Father Chaplin said: 'In recent times many anonymous photocopies of all sorts of pieces of paper have been circulated. In none of them is there the slightest evidence that the individuals we are talking about knew that these documents were being drawn up, or gave their consent. So I don't think any reasonably authoritative clerical or secular commission could see these papers as proof of anything.'", Russian Patriarch 'was KGB spy', The Guardian (London) , 12 February 1999</ref> 阿列克謝二世本人承認，他對蘇聯政府做出了妥協。他公開地對這些妥協表示懺悔。“為了保護一個事物，就有必要放棄另一些。又有哪些不僅身負自己，還有其他千萬人的命運的人，或者組織，在蘇聯統治的那些歲月中，沒有被迫做相似的事呢？然而，不僅對上帝，對於那些以往在教會的默許下，被迫妥協，被消聲，無力反抗，或者被迫表示忠誠，而造成痛苦的，我請求他們的原諒、理解、與祈禱。”<ref>From an interview of Patriarch Alexy II, given to "Izvestia" No 137, 10 June 1991, entitled "Patriarch Alexy II: – I Take upon Myself Responsibility for All that Happened", English translation from Nathaniel Davis, A Long Walk to Church: A Contemporary History of Russian Orthodoxy,(Oxford: Westview Press, 1995),p 89. See also [http://orthodoxinfo.com/ecumenism/roca_history.aspx History of the Russian Orthodox Church Abroad] {{Wayback|url=http://orthodoxinfo.com/ecumenism/roca_history.aspx |date=20090513181214 }}, by St. John (Maximovich) of Shanghai and San Francisco, 31 December 2007</ref>
